=== Iteration 1: Feature #6 - Training data preparation module ===
Feature #6 is complete. Here's what was implemented:

**`src/svapna/train/prepare.py`** — Training data preparation module that:
- Merges three data sources: conversation exchanges, memory pairs, and scored dreams
- Deduplicates via MD5 fingerprinting of normalized instruction+response text (keeps highest-weighted version)
- Applies exponential recency weighting (half-life decay: `2^(-age/half_life)`)
- Weights memory pairs higher than conversations (category-based: personality 3.0x, values 2.5x, etc., boosted by 1.5x)
- Weights dreams by quality score scaled by `dream_weight_factor`
- Sorts by weight descending, truncates to `max_examples`
- Outputs ChatML or instruction-format JSONL

**`tests/test_prepare.py`** — 23 tests covering all 6 required test cases plus edge cases:
- Merges all three sources correctly
- Deduplicates identical examples
- Recency weighting (exact half-life decay verified)
- Memory pairs weighted higher than conversations
- Valid ChatML and instruction-format output
- Respects max dataset size (keeps highest-weighted)

All 177 tests pass (23 new + 154 existing). Progress: **6/12 features complete**.

